text.section:
A licensed optometrist shall perform a minimum optometric examination which shall include:
Reviewing a patient's history, past prescriptions and specifications when available;
Visual analysis;
Ophthalmoscopy of internal eye;
Tonometry without anesthetic when indicated or for a patient over 40 years of age;
Muscle balance examination;
Writing of lens formula and other prescription data when needed as well as specific instructions for future care; and
Subsequent progress evaluation when indicated.
